725817f-c.title: Queens: 117th Street - Jamaica Avenue
725817f-c.text:
87-28 117th Street, adjoining the S.W. corner of Jamaica Avenue,
showing the Captain Briggs House. Captain Jeremiah Briggs, a sea
oaptain, built the house and lived here until his death in 1876 at
the age of 84. His daughter Nina married Joet Fowler in 1877 and the
couple made their home in this house. Joel Fowler was a Democfat and
Conveyor of Public Works.
Views 1,2: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1922
View 3: P.L.Sperr  August 22, 1932
